  <!-- PROJECTS -->
  <section id="projects" class="card">
    <h3>🚀 Key Projects</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><b>AWS RDS Automation & Cost Optimisation:</b> Designed and implemented a fully automated scheduling solution for non-production Amazon RDS environments using AWS Lambda and Amazon EventBridge. The solution automatically started and stopped databases based on predefined schedules, eliminating manual intervention and improving operational efficiency. This initiative reduced monthly database runtime from 744 hours to approximately 1.33 hours, delivering a 99.8% runtime reduction while improving security by limiting database availability to approved maintenance windows.</li>
      <li><b>Amazon RDS Weekday Scheduling Automation:</b> Engineered a weekday-only automation framework for Development and QA database environments to optimize cloud resource utilization and reduce unnecessary infrastructure costs. The solution automated database availability during business hours while ensuring systems remained offline outside operational requirements. This resulted in a 70% reduction in runtime and approximately 40% monthly cost savings on targeted AWS resources</li>
      <li><b>CloudWatch Monitoring & Proactive Alerting Framework:</b> Designed and maintained monitoring and alerting solutions using Amazon CloudWatch to improve visibility across cloud infrastructure and application services. Implemented proactive alerts, operational dashboards, and incident response processes that enabled early detection of performance issues, reduced troubleshooting time, and improved service reliability for business-critical educational platforms.</li>
      <li><b>Self-Service ITSM Portal:</b> Developed a self-service support portal integrated with Remedy ITSM to standardize incident and service request submissions across globally distributed support teams. The platform automated ticket creation, improved ticket quality through structured request forms, and reduced support workload by providing embedded knowledge articles and self-service FAQs.</li>
      <li><b>Tenant Statements Email Distribution System:</b> Supported the implementation of an automated tenant communication platform that distributed monthly tenant statements electronically. Responsibilities included validating and loading tenant contact data within NICOR, coordinating SMTP configuration with external providers, and conducting end-to-end testing. The solution eliminated manual distribution processes, improved delivery efficiency, and enhanced communication with tenants.</li>
      <li><b>Academy of Technology & Innovation (ATI) AWS Infrastructure Deployment:</b> Partnered with Silicon Overdrive during the deployment of the Academy of Technology & Innovation (ATI) cloud platform. Provisioned and configured AWS environments using Infrastructure as Code (Terraform), leveraging existing production infrastructure patterns to build and maintain development environments.Responsibilities included creating AWS accounts and environments, configuring IAM roles and permissions, managing access requirements, and supporting infrastructure deployment activities through GitHub-based workflows. Collaborated closely with engineering teams to ensure environment consistency, security, and operational readiness.</li>
    </ul>
